<title>
Rear Fog Light Assembly Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention1>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
To avoid danger of being burned, do not touch when the bulb is hot.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not touch glass surface of bulb to avoid deteriorate as the case may be unclear when bulb lights on at dirty condition.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention1>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A9206005001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear fog light nuts (2), and remove rear fog light assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect connector from rear fog light assembly (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A920011.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "60.200mm" ver = "03" gw = "214" gh = "154"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A9206005002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
Reverse removal procedure.
</ptxt>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
